# Agent Workflow

## After every code change

Before reporting a task as done:

1. Run validation from `web/`:
   ```bash
   cd web && npm run validate
   ```
2. If lint or build fails → fix and re-run until green.
3. Read linter diagnostics for edited files (`ReadLints`).

## Task completion checklist

```
- [ ] Changes are minimal and match project conventions
- [ ] `npm run validate` passes (lint + build)
- [ ] No secrets or build artifacts staged
- [ ] Git commit created (when automation requested or user asked)
- [ ] Commit message describes WHY, not just WHAT
```

## Automation mode

Auto-commit after successful validation when the user says:

- "完成并提交", "verify and commit", "ship it", "automate"
- Or explicitly includes "commit" / "提交" in the task

Otherwise: verify always, commit only on explicit request.

## Scope discipline

- App source: `web/` only (not repo root)
- Do not edit unrelated files
- Do not add tests/docs unless requested
- Comments in code: English only

## Failure handling

- Validation failed → fix root cause, do not skip steps
- Pre-commit hook rejected → fix issue, create NEW commit (never `--amend` unless rules allow)
- Missing deps → `cd web && npm install`, then retry validate
